  "root_text": {
    "an10.118:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10.118 ",
    "an10.118:0.2": "12. Paccorohaṇivagga ",
    "an10.118:0.3": "Orimatīrasutta ",
    "an10.118:1.1": "“Orimañca, bhikkhave, tīraṁ desessāmi pārimañca tīraṁ. ",
    "an10.118:1.2": "Taṁ suṇātha, sādhukaṁ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. ",
    "an10.118:1.3": "“Evaṁ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṁ. ",
    "an10.118:1.4": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
    "an10.118:2.1": "“Katamañca, bhikkhave, orimaṁ tīraṁ, katamañca pārimaṁ tīraṁ? ",
    "an10.118:2.2": "Micchādiṭṭhi orimaṁ tīraṁ, sammādiṭṭhi pārimaṁ tīraṁ …pe… ",
    "an10.118:2.3": "micchāvimutti orimaṁ tīraṁ, sammāvimutti pārimaṁ tīraṁ. ",
    "an10.118:2.4": "Idaṁ kho, bhikkhave, orimaṁ tīraṁ, idaṁ pārimaṁ tīranti. ",
    "an10.118:3.1": "Appakā te manussesu, ",
    "an10.118:3.2": "ye janā pāragāmino; ",
    "an10.118:3.3": "Athāyaṁ itarā pajā, ",
    "an10.118:3.4": "tīramevānudhāvati. ",
    "an10.118:4.1": "Ye ca kho sammadakkhāte, ",
    "an10.118:4.2": "dhamme dhammānuvattino; ",
    "an10.118:4.3": "Te janā pāramessanti, ",
    "an10.118:4.4": "maccudheyyaṁ suduttaraṁ. ",
    "an10.118:5.1": "Kaṇhaṁ dhammaṁ vippahāya, ",
    "an10.118:5.2": "sukkaṁ bhāvetha paṇḍito; ",
    "an10.118:5.3": "Okā anokamāgamma, ",
    "an10.118:5.4": "viveke yattha dūramaṁ. ",
    "an10.118:6.1": "Tatrābhiratimiccheyya, ",
    "an10.118:6.2": "hitvā kāme akiñcano; ",
    "an10.118:6.3": "Pariyodapeyya attānaṁ, ",
    "an10.118:6.4": "cittaklesehi paṇḍito. ",
    "an10.118:7.1": "Yesaṁ sambodhiyaṅgesu, ",
    "an10.118:7.2": "sammā cittaṁ subhāvitaṁ; ",
    "an10.118:7.3": "Ādānapaṭinissagge, ",
    "an10.118:7.4": "anupādāya ye ratā; ",
    "an10.118:7.5": "Khīṇāsavā jutimanto, ",
    "an10.118:7.6": "te loke parinibbutā”ti. ",
    "an10.118:7.7": "Chaṭṭhaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an10.118:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 10.118 ",
    "an10.118:0.2": "12. The Ceremony of Descent ",
    "an10.118:0.3": "The Near Shore ",
    "an10.118:1.1": "“Mendicants, I will teach you the near shore and the far shore. ",
    "an10.118:1.2": "Listen and apply your mind well, I will speak.” ",
    "an10.118:1.3": "“Yes, sir,” they replied. ",
    "an10.118:1.4": "The Buddha said this: ",
    "an10.118:2.1": "“And what, mendicants, is the near shore? What is the far shore? ",
    "an10.118:2.2": "Wrong view is the near shore, and right view is the far shore. … ",
    "an10.118:2.3": "Wrong freedom is the near shore, and right freedom is the far shore. ",
    "an10.118:2.4": "This is the near shore, and this is the far shore. ",
    "an10.118:3.1": "Few are those among humans ",
    "an10.118:3.2": "who cross to the far shore. ",
    "an10.118:3.3": "The rest just run ",
    "an10.118:3.4": "around on the near shore. ",
    "an10.118:4.1": "When the teaching is well explained, ",
    "an10.118:4.2": "those who practice accordingly ",
    "an10.118:4.3": "are the ones who will cross over ",
    "an10.118:4.4": "Death’s dominion so hard to pass. ",
    "an10.118:5.1": "Rid of dark qualities, ",
    "an10.118:5.2": "an astute person should develop the bright. ",
    "an10.118:5.3": "Leaving home behind ",
    "an10.118:5.4": "for the seclusion so hard to enjoy, ",
    "an10.118:6.1": "try to find satisfaction there, ",
    "an10.118:6.2": "having left behind sensual pleasures. ",
    "an10.118:6.3": "With no possessions, an astute person ",
    "an10.118:6.4": "should cleanse themselves of mental corruptions. ",
    "an10.118:7.1": "And those whose minds are rightly developed ",
    "an10.118:7.2": "in the awakening factors; ",
    "an10.118:7.3": "letting go of attachments, ",
    "an10.118:7.4": "they delight in not grasping. ",
    "an10.118:7.5": "With defilements ended, brilliant, ",
    "an10.118:7.6": "they are quenched in this world.” "
  },
